comments: Brunson (DAL) legally contests VanVleet (TOR) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Barnes (TOR) maintains legal guarding position moving laterally against Doncic's (DAL) path defending his driving shot attempt and marginal contact occurs.
Brunson (DAL) briefly engages with Siakam (TOR) after the pick and the contact does not affect his FOM.
Brunson (DAL) and Siakam (TOR) briefly engage in marginal contact prior to separating off ball.
Siakam (TOR) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Kleber (DAL) makes marginal contact with Siakam (TOR) off ball that does not affect his ability to get to the pass.
Brunson (DAL) and VanVleet (TOR) engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Kleber (DAL) places his hand to Siakam's (TOR) front off ball and the contact the does not affect his ability to move freely.
Siakam (TOR) establishes himself in a screening position in Brunson's (DAL) path and absorbs the contact.
Kleber (DAL) places his forearm to VanVleet's (TOR) front during his drive to the basket and marginal contact occurs.
Porzingis (DAL) places his hand to Boucher's (TOR) body after his gather and slides his hand off contesting his shot attempt. The contact is marginal.
Brunson (DAL) briefly grasps VanVleet's (TOR) jersey off ball and immediately disengages.
VanVleet (TOR) reaches in and avoids making contact to Brunson's (DAL) arm. The contact to Brunson's body is marginal.
Boucher (TOR) delivers contact to Porzingis' (DAL) body and the contact dislodges him as he gathers the pass. The illegal contact from Boucher causes Porzignis' right foot to step out of bounds.
Siakam (TOR) hands off the ball in Brunson's (DAL) path and is firming up when marginal contact occurs.
Porzingis (DAL) makes marginal contact to Barnes' (TOR) body as they pursue the loose ball and disengages.
Porzingis (DAL) makes marginal contact with Boucher's (TOR) arm after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Anunoby (TOR) briefly places his hand to Doncic's (DAL) backside and slides his hand off as they pursue the loose ball.

Boucher (TOR) places his hand to Porzingis' (DAL) back  and immediately slides his hand off prior to the inbound pass. The contact is marginal and does not affect Porzingis' ability to get to the pass.
Anunoby (TOR) briefly places two hands on Doncic (DAL) as he moves around the screen during the rebound. Doncic is able to move through the marginal contact.
Brunson (DAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Anunoby's (TOR) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.
Boucher (TOR) commits a take foul on Porzingis (DAL).
Anunoby (TOR) gathers the ball and takes fewer than three steps prior to his jump shot attempt.
Bullock (DAL) makes marginal contact with Anunoby's (TOR) body after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Barnes (TOR) makes marginal contact with Finney-Smith (DAL) and disengages as they pursue the rebound.
